So I think the big caveat here is like, we don't really know what the long-term trends are gonna be and it's possible things will change now that things are getting somewhat more back to normal.

77
00:08:49,613 --> 00:08:54,757
So for example, in 2018, there were 24 master deeds recorded in Medford

78
00:08:56,143 --> 00:08:59,725
2019 was 30, 29 in 2020, and then it's gone up.

79
00:08:59,805 --> 00:09:05,288
So 2021, there were 37, and 2022, there were 33 master deeds recorded.

80
00:09:05,508 --> 00:09:20,596
And I selected, just to kind of get a little idea of what this might include, I took one year of data, 2022, and looked at all the addresses of these master deeds to get a picture of what kind of building typologies we were talking about.

81
00:09:20,957 --> 00:09:23,398
And from my research, it looks like

82
